; assert-patch.zdbg - exercises patch-state assertions.
;
; Usage:
;   zdbg --batch -q -x examples/scripts/assert-patch.zdbg \
;       ./build/examples/testprog
;
; The script writes a single 0x90 (NOP) at RIP, asserts the
; resulting patch is recorded as applied, reverts it, and
; asserts it is now reverted.  Patching at the initial trap RIP
; is safe on Linux because we never resume after the patch.

l
check stopped
e rip 90
check patch 0 applied
pu 0
check patch 0 reverted
q
